27
00:00:45,920 --> 00:00:46,320
You know what?

28
00:00:46,480 --> 00:00:48,480
Let me write an article about the October Revolution in Russia.

29
00:00:49,520 --> 00:00:51,440
That can also do.

30
00:00:52,400 --> 00:00:53,120
Shizhi, you?

31
00:00:53,360 --> 00:00:55,360
Me? Maybe next time.

32
00:00:55,600 --> 00:00:56,720
I've been too busy recently.

33
00:00:58,560 --> 00:01:00,160
Which one of us is the busiest?

34
00:01:00,480 --> 00:01:00,960
You.

35
00:01:01,440 --> 00:01:02,320
You. It has to be.

36
00:01:03,120 --> 00:01:03,760
No.

37
00:01:03,920 --> 00:01:05,120
I think it's Shizhi.

38
00:01:06,240 --> 00:01:07,040
Why?

39
00:01:07,200 --> 00:01:09,360
Because he works hard every day

40
00:01:10,400 --> 00:01:13,440
and has to go to bed at ten o'clock at night.

41
00:01:14,480 --> 00:01:15,600
Otherwise his dear wife

42
00:01:15,680 --> 00:01:16,800
won't let him in.

43
00:01:16,880 --> 00:01:18,080
Are you two done?

44
00:01:18,640 --> 00:01:19,360
Come on in.

45
00:01:20,320 --> 00:01:21,840
I'm really impressed with you.

46
00:01:22,480 --> 00:01:23,120
Shiyan,

47
00:01:23,760 --> 00:01:25,520
can all these books be sold?

48
00:01:26,560 --> 00:01:27,440
Brother Ge said that in Changxindian

49
00:01:27,520 --> 00:01:28,160
there are thousands of people.

50
00:01:28,480 --> 00:01:29,440
Maybe it's not enough to sell.

51
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:30,640
I also bought some

52
00:01:30,720 --> 00:01:32,000
new magazines and newspapers.

53
00:01:32,880 --> 00:01:33,840
Sure enough, everyone is

54
00:01:33,920 --> 00:01:34,880
paying attention to this Wilson now.

55
00:01:35,120 --> 00:01:36,160
Even Liang Qichao

56
00:01:36,240 --> 00:01:38,160
also wrote an article called "League of Nations and China",

57
00:01:38,400 --> 00:01:39,600
saying that Wilson's League of Nations

58
00:01:39,920 --> 00:01:41,680
is the best means to realize a harmonious world.

59
00:01:42,160 --> 00:01:43,040
Didn't Mr. Shouchang write

60
00:01:43,120 --> 00:01:44,160
two articles about Russia?

61
00:01:44,960 --> 00:01:47,440
"New Era" and "Victory of Bolshevism".

62
00:01:47,520 --> 00:01:48,400
I bought them, too.

63
00:01:48,560 --> 00:01:49,680
But it seems that now everyone

64
00:01:49,760 --> 00:01:51,200
is paying more attention to Wilson.

65
00:01:51,680 --> 00:01:52,560
Brother Zhao.

66
00:01:52,800 --> 00:01:54,960
You see, there is still resistance

67
00:01:55,040 --> 00:01:55,920
to violent revolution.

68
00:01:56,640 --> 00:01:58,560
I said, what's wrong with your two brothers recently?

69
00:01:59,600 --> 00:02:00,400
When it comes to violent revolution,

70
00:02:00,480 --> 00:02:01,760
it's like seeing the plague.

71
00:02:01,920 --> 00:02:04,080
Think about it. Since ancient times,

72
00:02:04,480 --> 00:02:05,520
which reactionary regime

73
00:02:05,600 --> 00:02:06,960
has withdrawn from the historical stage by itself since ancient times?

74
00:02:07,600 --> 00:02:09,920
Since ancient times, which violent revolution

75
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:10,960
shed no blood?

76
00:02:11,280 --> 00:02:12,640
Reactionaries cannot be defeated without fighting.

77
00:02:11,637 --> 00:02:13,832
[Zhao Shiyan, styled Qin Sheng, Student at The High School Affiliated to Beijing Normal University

78
00:02:12,960 --> 00:02:14,080
This is common sense. It's law.

79
00:02:14,400 --> 00:02:15,120
Didn't the October Revolution in Russia

80
00:02:15,280 --> 00:02:16,240
overthrow the reactionaries

81
00:02:16,480 --> 00:02:17,360
and establish people's power?

82
00:02:17,440 --> 00:02:18,960
Can ordinary people live a good life?

83
00:02:19,440 --> 00:02:20,880
How do you know that the Russian people

84
00:02:20,960 --> 00:02:21,920
are living a good life now?

85
00:02:22,160 --> 00:02:24,000
But I hear all countries are blockading them now.

86
00:02:24,320 --> 00:02:25,280
Internal rebellion continues.

87
00:02:25,520 --> 00:02:26,320
Let me tell you.

88
00:02:26,560 --> 00:02:28,240
Take a long-term view of the problem.

89
00:02:28,480 --> 00:02:29,840
The replacement of old and new social systems

90
00:02:29,920 --> 00:02:31,840
is a long struggle.

91
00:02:31,920 --> 00:02:32,800
There is no problem with your long-term vision.

92
00:02:32,880 --> 00:02:33,760
All right, let's not argue.

93
00:02:34,320 --> 00:02:36,240
Grandpas, help me push hard.

94
00:02:36,560 --> 00:02:37,360
Come on, come on.

95
00:02:37,440 --> 00:02:38,000
Let's go.

96
00:02:40,640 --> 00:02:41,680
Brother Juren.

97
00:02:41,760 --> 00:02:44,480
I'm called here today, and I'm given a painting.

98
00:02:44,880 --> 00:02:47,360
But I'm afraid that's not your intention.

99
00:02:47,747 --> 00:02:49,290
[Xu Shichang, President of the Republic of China]

100
00:02:48,800 --> 00:02:49,600
Clever.

101
00:02:51,120 --> 00:02:54,080
Botang, Lu Zhengxiang is going to Paris soon.

102
00:02:54,400 --> 00:02:55,200
This diplomatic mess

103
00:02:55,360 --> 00:02:56,960
depends solely on Chen Zhuan, the acting minister.

104
00:02:57,360 --> 00:02:58,640
It won't hold up.

105
00:02:57,726 --> 00:02:59,640
[Wang Daxie, styled Botang, Chairman of the Foreign Affairs Committee of the Republic of China]

106
00:02:58,960 --> 00:03:00,080
So at this juncture,

107
00:03:00,480 --> 00:03:02,480
you can't think about hiding at leisure.

108
00:03:03,040 --> 00:03:04,800
Your Foreign Affairs Committee

109
00:03:05,760 --> 00:03:07,040
is the decision-making body of foreign affairs

110
00:03:07,120 --> 00:03:08,880
in my presidential office.

111
00:03:10,000 --> 00:03:12,000
How the negotiation goes in Paris is up to you.

112
00:03:12,720 --> 00:03:14,640
Brother Juren, you're kidding me.

113
00:03:16,240 --> 00:03:17,440
Cao Rulin

114
00:03:17,680 --> 00:03:19,280
will be able to veto my proposal.

115
00:03:19,920 --> 00:03:22,720
I think it's hard for me to do anything.

116
00:03:25,200 --> 00:03:26,400
Can't be pessimistic.

117
00:03:27,680 --> 00:03:29,840
It's hard to be treated as a victorious country.

118
00:03:30,480 --> 00:03:31,920
You have to do something.

119
00:03:32,960 --> 00:03:34,880
This is a godsend opportunity.

120
00:03:35,440 --> 00:03:36,720
Heaven is responsible for it.

121
00:03:38,640 --> 00:03:41,040
Now there is a difficult problem to decide.

122
00:03:41,200 --> 00:03:41,840
Go ahead.

123
00:03:42,320 --> 00:03:45,520
We went to Paris for peace talks with five people.

124
00:03:45,920 --> 00:03:48,800
But they gave our negotiators

125
00:03:49,040 --> 00:03:50,160
only two people.

126
00:03:51,040 --> 00:03:53,120
Who should be the permanent representative in charge of the talks?

127
00:03:53,520 --> 00:03:55,520
This candidate is crucial.

128
00:03:56,560 --> 00:03:58,720
Lu Zhengxiang is the chief representative.

129
00:03:59,440 --> 00:04:00,640
There is one seat left.

130
00:04:01,200 --> 00:04:03,040
Let them take turns to attend.

131
00:04:03,760 --> 00:04:04,960
Absolutely not.

132
00:04:05,280 --> 00:04:06,480
This Lu Zhengxiang is in poor health

133
00:04:06,800 --> 00:04:08,880
and will be staying in Switzerland for a long time.

134
00:04:09,440 --> 00:04:10,880
Wang Zhengting knows nothing about diplomacy.

135
00:04:11,120 --> 00:04:12,240
He can't take the position.

136
00:04:12,480 --> 00:04:13,680
What do you mean?

137
00:04:14,720 --> 00:04:15,920
My opinion is

138
00:04:16,080 --> 00:04:18,800
let Gu Weijun take second place,

139
00:04:19,280 --> 00:04:20,640
let him be the main negotiator.

140
00:04:23,600 --> 00:04:25,120
There must be no trouble in the south.

141
00:04:25,760 --> 00:04:26,640
So it's up to you,

142
00:04:26,800 --> 00:04:28,640
the president, to make decisions.

143
00:04:29,120 --> 00:04:30,560
Tell them to take care of the overall situation.

144
00:04:40,000 --> 00:04:40,640
Very well.

145
00:04:42,320 --> 00:04:46,240
I will do as Chairman Wang said.

146
00:04:51,280 --> 00:04:52,800
This painting is too good.

147
00:04:55,040 --> 00:04:55,360
Yannian.

148
00:04:56,000 --> 00:04:57,520
Come and help me classify these new books.

149
00:04:57,680 --> 00:04:58,320
Be sure to check it out.

150
00:04:58,400 --> 00:04:58,640
Got it.

151
00:04:59,040 --> 00:04:59,440
When I finish distributing the newspapers.

152
00:04:59,520 --> 00:04:59,600
OK.

153
00:05:00,560 --> 00:05:01,200
Qiaonian.

154
00:05:01,520 --> 00:05:02,480
Come and share the newspapers with me when you are finished.

155
00:05:02,560 --> 00:05:02,880
OK.

156
00:05:04,400 --> 00:05:04,640
Hello, sir.

157
00:05:04,720 --> 00:05:05,200
Hello.

158
00:05:07,440 --> 00:05:08,080
Thank you.

159
00:05:10,960 --> 00:05:11,120
Hello, sir.

160
00:05:11,200 --> 00:05:11,760
Hello.

161
00:05:12,400 --> 00:05:12,800
Hello, sir.

162
00:05:14,000 --> 00:05:15,200
Bai Lan, you've worked so hard.

163
00:05:15,440 --> 00:05:15,840
Hello, sir.

164
00:05:16,000 --> 00:05:16,480
Hello, sir.

165
00:05:16,640 --> 00:05:17,600
Hello, everyone. Hello, Mr. Shouchang.

166
00:05:20,400 --> 00:05:21,040
Mr. Shouchang,

167
00:05:21,600 --> 00:05:22,880
I haven't seen you for some time.

168
00:05:24,160 --> 00:05:25,280
It's said that

169
00:05:25,360 --> 00:05:26,560
you are the busiest person in Peking University these days.

170
00:05:26,800 --> 00:05:27,760
Why do you say this?

171
00:05:28,000 --> 00:05:30,560
Look, you're the library director,

172
00:05:30,880 --> 00:05:31,760
the editor of "New Youth"

173
00:05:31,840 --> 00:05:33,120
and "Weekly Review",

174
00:05:33,680 --> 00:05:35,200
and the editor and writer

175
00:05:35,280 --> 00:05:36,400
of the new magazine "Citizen".

176
00:05:36,960 --> 00:05:38,160
Recently, you initiated

177
00:05:38,240 --> 00:05:39,840
and established the Marquez Research Society

178
00:05:40,160 --> 00:05:42,800
based on the Youth Reading Club.

179
00:05:41,389 --> 00:05:43,083
[Chen Qiaonian, second son of Chen Duxiu]

180
00:05:43,360 --> 00:05:44,640
And you often

181
00:05:44,720 --> 00:05:47,040
go to the Changxindian factory for research and investigation.

182
00:05:47,600 --> 00:05:49,200
Would you say that there is anyone busier than you?

183
00:05:49,440 --> 00:05:50,880
Not the Marquez Society.

184
00:05:50,960 --> 00:05:52,080
It's the Marx Society.

185
00:05:52,640 --> 00:05:54,560
I remember it was the Marquez Society.

186
00:05:54,960 --> 00:05:56,400
It's Marx.

187
00:05:56,640 --> 00:05:58,240
Mr. Wang deliberately called it Marquez.

188
00:05:58,320 --> 00:05:59,200
Not Marx.

189
00:05:59,520 --> 00:06:00,880
Just to make others think that we

190
00:06:00,960 --> 00:06:03,280
are a society that studies Malthusian population theory.

191
00:06:03,680 --> 00:06:05,040
So we won't get into trouble with the authorities.

192
00:06:03,757 --> 00:06:05,115
[Chen Yannian, eldest son of Chen Duxiu]

193
00:06:05,520 --> 00:06:07,200
Marxist research will cause trouble.

194
00:06:07,760 --> 00:06:09,280
During this time, I read some Marx's books

195
00:06:09,360 --> 00:06:10,480
here with Mr. Dazhao,

196
00:06:10,800 --> 00:06:11,840
and I was deeply inspired.

197
00:06:12,080 --> 00:06:12,800
Nice!

198
00:06:13,520 --> 00:06:14,000
It's time to start

199
00:06:14,080 --> 00:06:15,600
read Marxist books consciously.

200
00:06:16,640 --> 00:06:18,720
Students, in the future, our reading club

201
00:06:19,040 --> 00:06:20,480
will focus on recommending

202
00:06:20,800 --> 00:06:22,960
and letting everyone read more books on Marxism.

203
00:06:24,160 --> 00:06:24,960
Mr. Shouchang.

204
00:06:25,520 --> 00:06:26,480
Mr. Shouchang.

205
00:06:29,360 --> 00:06:30,000
Sir.

206
00:06:30,240 --> 00:06:32,480
Runzhi and I want to ask you something.

207
00:06:33,440 --> 00:06:34,000
Go on.

208
00:06:34,240 --> 00:06:35,520
Here's the thing, Mr. Shouchang.

209
00:06:34,347 --> 00:06:36,634
[Mao Zedong, styled Runzhi, Peking University Library Assistant]

210
00:06:35,840 --> 00:06:38,000
I just received a letter from Hunan.

211
00:06:38,400 --> 00:06:40,800
I think this letter is particularly reasonable.

212
00:06:41,040 --> 00:06:43,040
So I wanted to come and discuss a solution with you.

213
00:06:43,360 --> 00:06:44,800
Please have a look, sir.

214
00:06:45,440 --> 00:06:46,560
My friend Xiong Guangchu

215
00:06:46,720 --> 00:06:47,920
is a member of the Xinmin Society.

216
00:06:49,040 --> 00:06:50,160
In his letter,

217
00:06:50,400 --> 00:06:52,800
he suggested that teachers and students of various colleges and universities

218
00:06:52,960 --> 00:06:54,160
should first promote the establishment of reading rooms

219
00:06:54,400 --> 00:06:55,760
in towns and villages all over the country,

220
00:06:56,080 --> 00:06:58,240
so as to publicize New Culture and advanced ideas

221
00:06:58,480 --> 00:06:59,840
to the people all over the country

222
00:07:00,080 --> 00:07:01,680
and gradually improve people's quality.

223
00:07:02,080 --> 00:07:02,720
Sir,

224
00:07:02,960 --> 00:07:04,880
I think Runzhi's suggestion is particularly good.

225
00:07:05,120 --> 00:07:06,640
At present, the enlightenment of New Culture thought

226
00:07:05,360 --> 00:07:08,164
[Deng Zhongxia, styled Zhonghao, Student at Peking University]

227
00:07:06,800 --> 00:07:08,720
is mainly among students and young people.

228
00:07:09,200 --> 00:07:11,360
If we can gradually improve people's quality

229
00:07:11,600 --> 00:07:13,120
and publicize new ideas and culture

230
00:07:13,360 --> 00:07:14,720
by setting up reading rooms,

231
00:07:15,040 --> 00:07:16,960
this would be a wonderful thing.

232
00:07:17,600 --> 00:07:18,400
The suggestion is good.

233
00:07:18,560 --> 00:07:20,560
But it's not easy to set up reading rooms

234
00:07:20,640 --> 00:07:22,960
in all towns and villages across the country.

235
00:07:23,440 --> 00:07:25,680
Mr. Shouchang, at least

236
00:07:26,000 --> 00:07:27,440
someone needs to come out and take the lead.

237
00:07:28,400 --> 00:07:31,280
This is a good suggestion

238
00:07:31,360 --> 00:07:32,560
for New Culture to go public.

239
00:07:33,280 --> 00:07:34,320
But this proposal

240
00:07:34,560 --> 00:07:36,560
will consume a lot of manpower and financial resources.

241
00:07:36,960 --> 00:07:39,120
The key, Runzhi, is, as you said,

242
00:07:39,840 --> 00:07:41,200
who will take the lead?

243
00:07:42,080 --> 00:07:43,280
Runzhi's suggestion is

244
00:07:44,320 --> 00:07:45,920
our Peking University will take the lead.

245
00:07:46,880 --> 00:07:49,520
Spreading New Culture is the responsibility of Peking University.

246
00:07:50,240 --> 00:07:51,200
But this thing,

247
00:07:51,520 --> 00:07:53,120
you should report it to Mr. Cai.

248
00:07:53,360 --> 00:07:54,400
Let him decide.

249
00:07:54,720 --> 00:07:56,720
OK, I'll write to Mr. Cai now.

250
00:07:57,680 --> 00:07:58,320
Good.

251
00:08:15,280 --> 00:08:16,000
Sir.

252
00:08:16,240 --> 00:08:16,960
Fellow students.

253
00:08:17,440 --> 00:08:19,040
I've been thinking about a problem recently.

254
00:08:19,520 --> 00:08:20,320
Our reading club

255
00:08:20,400 --> 00:08:22,160
cannot simply stop at ideological confrontation.

256
00:08:22,560 --> 00:08:23,440
More importantly,

257
00:08:23,600 --> 00:08:25,840
we combine truth with practice.

258
00:08:26,320 --> 00:08:27,280
So I have an initiative.

259
00:08:27,600 --> 00:08:29,680
We will set up a work-study mutual aid society.

260
00:08:30,160 --> 00:08:31,600
We will form a mutual aid group

261
00:08:31,920 --> 00:08:33,680
according to the theory of mutual aid

262
00:08:34,240 --> 00:08:36,160
to experiment with mutual assistance communism.

263
00:08:36,640 --> 00:08:37,760
I wonder if you agree.

264
00:08:38,080 --> 00:08:40,160
Yannian, Wang Guangqi mentioned

265
00:08:40,240 --> 00:08:41,360
your idea before.

266
00:08:41,920 --> 00:08:43,360
I think there is nothing wrong in theory.

267
00:08:43,760 --> 00:08:45,200
But will the actual operation

268
00:08:45,520 --> 00:08:46,400
be difficult?

269
00:08:47,040 --> 00:08:48,240
I discussed this problem with him.

270
00:08:48,640 --> 00:08:50,240
He wants to make this operation big.

271
00:08:50,720 --> 00:08:52,000
But it will also be difficult.

272
00:08:52,480 --> 00:08:54,720
I just want to do a small-scale experiment first,

273
00:08:55,280 --> 00:08:57,280
and just try it out in our reading club

274
00:08:57,360 --> 00:08:58,640
and French study hall.

275
00:08:59,040 --> 00:09:00,400
Today, I will just make an initiative first.

276
00:09:00,720 --> 00:09:02,320
If everyone thinks it's feasible,

277
00:09:02,720 --> 00:09:04,000
then I'll go back to draft the articles of association immediately.

278
00:09:05,360 --> 00:09:06,560
He's advocating such a thing.

279
00:09:06,720 --> 00:09:07,440
He did a good job.

280
00:09:07,760 --> 00:09:08,800
Like this, also like that.

281
00:09:09,040 --> 00:09:09,760
I think it's pretty good.

282
00:09:10,320 --> 00:09:10,960
I'm willing to have a try.

283
00:09:11,200 --> 00:09:11,280
Right.

284
00:09:11,760 --> 00:09:13,440
I think this Yannian's initiative

285
00:09:13,840 --> 00:09:15,520
is a very good combination of theory and practice.

286
00:09:15,760 --> 00:09:16,480
I have an initiative.

287
00:09:16,960 --> 00:09:17,440
Please.

288
00:09:25,200 --> 00:09:27,120
I think New Culture must be combined

289
00:09:27,360 --> 00:09:29,120
with the workers and peasants in order to reach the masses.

290
00:09:29,440 --> 00:09:31,520
I did research in Changxindian a while ago

291
00:09:31,920 --> 00:09:32,720
and also learned a lot.

292
00:09:32,960 --> 00:09:34,560
Changxindian has nearly 4,000 workers.

293
00:09:35,120 --> 00:09:36,320
The workers work long hours

294
00:09:36,560 --> 00:09:37,280
and paid low salaries.

295
00:09:37,440 --> 00:09:39,760
Everyone works ten hours every summer,

296
00:09:39,840 --> 00:09:41,280
and work about eleven to twelve hours in winter.

297
00:09:41,600 --> 00:09:44,400
But the wages only range from three cents to one yuan.

298
00:09:44,720 --> 00:09:46,400
Many workers work all day

299
00:09:46,880 --> 00:09:47,760
without food and clothing.

300
00:09:48,080 --> 00:09:49,040
What surprises me even more is

301
00:09:49,440 --> 00:09:50,720
the number of illiterate workers.

302
00:09:50,960 --> 00:09:52,240
We took two hundred copies of New Youth.

303
00:09:52,720 --> 00:09:54,000
Not even the last half was sold.

304
00:09:54,240 --> 00:09:55,440
I really think we don't know much

305
00:09:55,520 --> 00:09:56,800
about this group.

306
00:09:56,960 --> 00:09:58,480
Therefore, Zhongxie and I are going to organize

307
00:09:58,560 --> 00:09:59,600
a lecture group on civilian education,

308
00:09:59,840 --> 00:10:01,840
taking Changxindian as a pilot to give a series of lectures

309
00:10:02,480 --> 00:10:03,680
and conduct in-depth investigation.

310
00:10:04,080 --> 00:10:05,120
Shiyan is absolutely right.

311
00:10:05,760 --> 00:10:08,000
I think research and lectures

312
00:10:08,400 --> 00:10:09,280
should be combined.

313
00:10:09,680 --> 00:10:10,800
This form of lectures

314
00:10:11,040 --> 00:10:12,800
may be even more urgent for civilians,

315
00:10:13,360 --> 00:10:15,840
because there are few civilians who can read now.

316
00:10:16,080 --> 00:10:18,320
There are even less who can read publications

317
00:10:18,400 --> 00:10:19,040
and printed material.

318
00:10:19,280 --> 00:10:20,880
So if you want to carry out universal education,

319
00:10:21,440 --> 00:10:22,960
you have to start with lectures.

320
00:10:23,360 --> 00:10:24,240
And I think

321
00:10:24,320 --> 00:10:26,640
the organizational form of this lecture group on civilian education

322
00:10:26,960 --> 00:10:27,840
doesn't have to be complicated.

323
00:10:28,240 --> 00:10:29,200
A few people

324
00:10:29,440 --> 00:10:30,480
can prepare a topic in advance for a group

325
00:10:30,720 --> 00:10:31,840
and go to a crowded place

326
00:10:32,080 --> 00:10:35,120
such as a temple fair to give a speech.

327
00:10:35,360 --> 00:10:36,000
Right.

328
00:10:36,160 --> 00:10:37,440
The topic doesn't have to be complicated.

329
00:10:38,080 --> 00:10:41,360
We start with general knowledge and current affairs.

330
00:10:41,600 --> 00:10:42,560
We should let

331
00:10:42,800 --> 00:10:44,640
ordinary poor workers and civilians

332
00:10:45,040 --> 00:10:46,960
know some current affairs

333
00:10:47,120 --> 00:10:48,080
and general knowledge,

334
00:10:48,320 --> 00:10:50,160
and then realize their status

335
00:10:50,240 --> 00:10:51,280
and the source of social diseases.

336
00:10:51,520 --> 00:10:53,360
Getting them to do something positive

337
00:10:53,520 --> 00:10:55,120
will not achieve our goal.

338
00:10:57,440 --> 00:10:59,200
I have spent every day in Changsha

339
00:10:59,440 --> 00:11:01,280
among ordinary people over the years.

340
00:11:01,600 --> 00:11:02,320
Their suffering.

341
00:11:02,720 --> 00:11:03,440
Their joy.

342
00:11:03,920 --> 00:11:05,600
I feel the same way more or less.

343
00:11:05,920 --> 00:11:06,560
And

344
00:11:06,800 --> 00:11:08,880
I have a better understanding of what they really want.

345
00:11:09,280 --> 00:11:11,280
So, I couldn't agree more

346
00:11:11,360 --> 00:11:12,240
to Shiyan's and Yannian's proposals.

347
00:11:12,720 --> 00:11:13,520
I want to join

348
00:11:14,480 --> 00:11:15,280
both societies.

349
00:11:16,400 --> 00:11:17,200
I want to join.

350
00:11:17,520 --> 00:11:18,000
I want to join.

351
00:11:20,880 --> 00:11:21,520
Yannian.

352
00:11:22,080 --> 00:11:22,720
You asked me just now.

353
00:11:22,800 --> 00:11:24,160
What do you think of your proposal?

354
00:11:24,720 --> 00:11:27,920
I want to applaud you and Shiyan.

355
00:11:38,160 --> 00:11:38,960
Students.

356
00:11:39,760 --> 00:11:41,520
Why should I applaud these two students?

357
00:11:41,920 --> 00:11:42,960
Because these two students

358
00:11:43,360 --> 00:11:45,200
all saw a problem.

359
00:11:45,680 --> 00:11:49,680
That is, theory and practice should be combined.

360
00:11:50,160 --> 00:11:52,400
As we said at the rally,

361
00:11:52,640 --> 00:11:55,200
celebrating the victory in the war in Europe,

362
00:11:55,520 --> 00:11:56,800
the New Culture Movement

363
00:11:57,120 --> 00:11:59,040
has now reached a turning point.

364
00:11:59,440 --> 00:12:02,800
That turning point is that the New Culture Movement

365
00:12:03,680 --> 00:12:05,120
is going to the public.

366
00:12:05,920 --> 00:12:06,720
Zhongxie,

367
00:12:07,280 --> 00:12:09,280
Mr. Cai replied to the letter.

368
00:12:09,760 --> 00:12:10,640
What did Mr. Cai say?

369
00:12:10,880 --> 00:12:12,240
Mr. Cai fully supports it

370
00:12:12,400 --> 00:12:13,920
and urges us all

371
00:12:14,160 --> 00:12:15,600
to go out as soon as possible.

372
00:12:16,160 --> 00:12:18,160
I have just listened to your classmates' speeches.

373
00:12:18,560 --> 00:12:21,120
I am both excited and admired.

374
00:12:22,080 --> 00:12:22,800
Excited

375
00:12:22,880 --> 00:12:25,120
to see everyone's insights.

376
00:12:25,760 --> 00:12:26,640
Admired

377
00:12:26,960 --> 00:12:29,040
to see everyone's pioneering spirit.

378
00:12:29,760 --> 00:12:31,120
You choose to go out.

379
00:12:31,600 --> 00:12:33,200
That means giving up a lot.

380
00:12:33,840 --> 00:12:36,000
It means that you have chosen a difficult road,

381
00:12:36,560 --> 00:12:38,400
and given up a comfortable road like Shizhi.

382
00:12:38,880 --> 00:12:41,360
It means that you have chosen a pioneering road

383
00:12:42,000 --> 00:12:44,080
and given up a safe road.

384
00:12:44,640 --> 00:12:46,400
It means that you have chosen

385
00:12:46,640 --> 00:12:48,880
the road to struggle against difficulties,

386
00:12:49,520 --> 00:12:53,040
and given up the comfortable road of sitting around and talking.

387
00:12:53,680 --> 00:12:54,240
Students,

388
00:12:54,720 --> 00:12:56,720
we are going out of the study halls

389
00:12:57,040 --> 00:12:58,080
to the grass-roots.

390
00:12:58,400 --> 00:13:01,600
I know this road is hard and bitter.

391
00:13:01,920 --> 00:13:02,960
But I firmly believe,

392
00:13:03,440 --> 00:13:04,880
no matter how difficult or bitter the road is,

393
00:13:05,120 --> 00:13:06,400
you cannot be beaten,

394
00:13:06,960 --> 00:13:09,040
because I saw everyone's courage.

395
00:13:10,400 --> 00:13:12,880
Students, I sincerely hope that everyone

396
00:13:13,360 --> 00:13:15,440
be able to step on the dirt with both feet,

397
00:13:15,920 --> 00:13:17,120
and walk

398
00:13:17,840 --> 00:13:19,120
every step of the way

399
00:13:19,600 --> 00:13:20,880
step by step.

400
00:13:21,360 --> 00:13:24,240
And I believe that victory will definitely belong to us

401
00:13:25,280 --> 00:13:28,800
because we're already on our way.

402
00:13:29,360 --> 00:13:31,680
Hurrah!

403
00:13:34,720 --> 00:13:36,240
Hurrah!

404
00:13:47,840 --> 00:13:49,040
Let's solve a problem.

405
00:13:49,520 --> 00:13:51,280
We must first know the essence of this problem.

406
00:13:51,680 --> 00:13:53,840
Then this is the purpose of going to the grass-roots.

407
00:13:54,000 --> 00:13:55,200
Today, Shugui helped us

408
00:13:55,280 --> 00:13:56,880
make an appointment with many workers' representatives.

409
00:13:57,360 --> 00:13:58,320
Be sure to ask questions.

410
00:13:58,720 --> 00:13:59,920
Only when there are problems will there be knowledge.

411
00:14:00,000 --> 00:14:00,960
Sir, Mr. Shouchang.

412
00:14:01,520 --> 00:14:02,000
Sir.

413
00:14:02,160 --> 00:14:03,200
Runzhi. Zhongxie.

414
00:14:03,360 --> 00:14:04,560
Mr. Shouchang.

415
00:14:07,520 --> 00:14:08,400
Come, Runzhi.

416
00:14:08,720 --> 00:14:10,000
I'll ask Zhongxie to call you here.

417
00:14:10,160 --> 00:14:12,480
I want to invite you to participate in our activities in Peking University.

418
00:14:12,880 --> 00:14:13,600
I'm not bothering you, am I?

419
00:14:14,080 --> 00:14:14,720
Not at all.

420
00:14:20,400 --> 00:14:22,480
How long has Runzhi been in Beijing?

421
00:14:22,720 --> 00:14:23,920
It's been more than half a year.

422
00:14:24,080 --> 00:14:25,120
Have you ever been to Changxindian?

423
00:14:25,360 --> 00:14:27,200
I've been there with Zhongxie and Zhao Shiyan.

424
00:14:27,520 --> 00:14:28,480
But they were all short visits.

425
00:14:29,040 --> 00:14:31,040
It's a rare opportunity to know that you are going

426
00:14:31,360 --> 00:14:32,240
to do special research this time.

427
00:14:32,320 --> 00:14:34,240
I can also get a closer look

428
00:14:34,560 --> 00:14:35,280
of the state of workers here.

429
00:14:35,520 --> 00:14:36,400
Marx said

430
00:14:36,720 --> 00:14:37,840
the industrial working class

431
00:14:37,920 --> 00:14:39,840
is the most advanced class in the world.

432
00:14:40,320 --> 00:14:41,200
But is this sentence

433
00:14:41,440 --> 00:14:43,920
in line with China's reality?

434
00:14:44,080 --> 00:14:46,080
I think it's a real problem.

435
00:14:46,320 --> 00:14:48,160
We have been to Changxindian several times before.

436
00:14:48,480 --> 00:14:50,400
I think Marx has a point.

437
00:14:51,920 --> 00:14:52,800
Does he?

438
00:14:53,040 --> 00:14:55,120
Let's experience that with our own hearts.

439
00:14:56,320 --> 00:14:57,440
You are in charge of recording today.

440
00:14:57,760 --> 00:14:58,400
Very well.

441
00:15:04,040 --> 00:15:07,589
[Changxindian workers' dormitories]

442
00:15:15,680 --> 00:15:17,200
This is for the guests.

443
00:15:17,360 --> 00:15:18,080
Go play.

444
00:15:19,520 --> 00:15:20,560
Please come in, please.

445
00:15:21,280 --> 00:15:21,920
Everyone.

446
00:15:22,880 --> 00:15:25,440
This is the one I always tell you about.

447
00:15:25,600 --> 00:15:27,840
Professor Li Dazhao of Peking University.

448
00:15:28,080 --> 00:15:29,600
Hello, masters.

449
00:15:29,840 --> 00:15:30,320
These gentlemen

450
00:15:30,560 --> 00:15:31,920
are Professor Li's students.

451
00:15:32,240 --> 00:15:33,200
Mr. Dazhao, sit down.

452
00:15:33,280 --> 00:15:33,920
Sit, sit.

453
00:15:34,000 --> 00:15:35,200
Excuse me, masters.

454
00:15:35,600 --> 00:15:36,480
Sit inside, sit inside.

455
00:15:37,200 --> 00:15:37,760
Help yourself.

456
00:15:38,320 --> 00:15:39,040
Thank you.

457
00:15:39,120 --> 00:15:40,000
You're welcome.

458
00:15:40,080 --> 00:15:40,560
You're so kind.

459
00:15:40,800 --> 00:15:41,360
Sit down, sit down.

460
00:15:41,520 --> 00:15:42,640
Professor Li, they came here

461
00:15:42,720 --> 00:15:44,000
just to ask us

462
00:15:44,320 --> 00:15:45,520
if we have any difficulties

463
00:15:45,760 --> 00:15:46,880
to chat with us.

464
00:15:47,920 --> 00:15:49,280
Professor Li, these

465
00:15:49,360 --> 00:15:50,960
are the old workers on our railway.

466
00:15:51,040 --> 00:15:52,880
Please feel free to ask if you have any questions.

467
00:15:53,040 --> 00:15:53,440
Good.

468
00:15:54,080 --> 00:15:55,440
Hello, masters.

469
00:15:55,920 --> 00:15:56,400
Hello.

470
00:15:56,880 --> 00:15:57,280
Give this to the gentleman.

471
00:15:57,680 --> 00:15:59,120
Actually, we're here

472
00:15:59,440 --> 00:16:01,120
just to talk to the masters.

473
00:16:01,280 --> 00:16:03,360
Just to chit-chat.

474
00:16:04,320 --> 00:16:05,200
Everyone knows that

475
00:16:05,520 --> 00:16:06,960
this world war is over.

476
00:16:07,200 --> 00:16:09,440
China, on the other hand, has become a victorious country.

477
00:16:09,520 --> 00:16:10,400
But how did our China

478
00:16:10,480 --> 00:16:12,240
become a victorious country?

479
00:16:12,720 --> 00:16:14,240
That's because China

480
00:16:14,320 --> 00:16:15,760
sent several hundreds of thousands of workers

481
00:16:16,480 --> 00:16:17,440
to the European battlefield.

482
00:16:17,680 --> 00:16:19,200
Because of these workers,

483
00:16:19,440 --> 00:16:22,000
with their own blood, sweat, and life,

484
00:16:22,560 --> 00:16:24,160
won honour

485
00:16:24,800 --> 00:16:26,400
for our country.

486
00:16:26,720 --> 00:16:27,920
Personally, I also think

487
00:16:28,080 --> 00:16:29,840
that our Chinese workers

488
00:16:30,000 --> 00:16:32,400
are the most hardworking people in the world,

489
00:16:32,960 --> 00:16:34,480
the greatest workers in the world,

490
00:16:34,720 --> 00:16:36,960
who should be widely respected by society.

491
00:16:37,200 --> 00:16:37,920
Professor Li.

492
00:16:38,160 --> 00:16:39,760
Ah, you're too kind.

493
00:16:39,920 --> 00:16:41,520
If you have any questions, just ask.

494
00:16:41,760 --> 00:16:43,440
We don't have anything to hide.

495
00:16:43,680 --> 00:16:44,400
Okay, okay, okay.

496
00:16:45,040 --> 00:16:46,960
I want to ask you a question first.

497
00:16:47,360 --> 00:16:49,680
What specific jobs are you engaged in?

498
00:16:51,360 --> 00:16:53,200
Changxindian locomotives and rolling stock factories

499
00:16:53,280 --> 00:16:55,360
were an early modern industry in China,

500
00:16:55,760 --> 00:16:57,760
and were one of the important breeding grounds

501
00:16:57,840 --> 00:16:59,600
of China's early industrial workforce.

502
00:17:00,240 --> 00:17:01,760
After the October Revolution in Russia,

503
00:17:02,400 --> 00:17:04,960
Chinese pioneers began to realize

504
00:17:05,040 --> 00:17:07,440
the great power of the working class.

505
00:17:08,400 --> 00:17:09,840
In March 1919,

506
00:17:10,400 --> 00:17:11,680
under the guidance of Li Dazhao,

507
00:17:12,160 --> 00:17:15,200
Deng Zhongxia organized and established a lecture group

508
00:17:15,280 --> 00:17:17,200
on civilian education in Peking University,

509
00:17:17,440 --> 00:17:19,760
and began to give lectures in Changxindian.

510
00:17:20,640 --> 00:17:23,040
In the process of integrating with the working masses,

511
00:17:23,280 --> 00:17:25,120
a group of intellectuals

512
00:17:25,520 --> 00:17:26,320
such as Li Dazhao and Deng Zhongxia,

513
00:17:26,400 --> 00:17:27,840
who initially came into contact with Marxism,

514
00:17:28,480 --> 00:17:30,800
further changed their thoughts and feelings

515
00:17:30,880 --> 00:17:32,160
to the working class.

516
00:17:32,720 --> 00:17:35,440
At the same time, some workers such as Ge Shugui,

517
00:17:35,760 --> 00:17:38,320
thanks to the education of Marxism-Leninism,

518
00:17:38,560 --> 00:17:40,080
promoted class consciousness

519
00:17:40,560 --> 00:17:43,600
and became advanced members of the working class.

520
00:17:47,440 --> 00:17:49,280
Shiyan, do you know anything about the countryside?

521
00:17:49,520 --> 00:17:51,600
My family have always been in cities, where I've studied since childhood.

522
00:17:51,760 --> 00:17:53,120
I really don't know much about the countryside.

523
00:17:53,600 --> 00:17:55,280
I think in our country,

524
00:17:55,520 --> 00:17:57,600
workers live like farmers.

525
00:17:57,920 --> 00:17:58,880
There's not much difference.

526
00:17:59,040 --> 00:17:59,920
How can you see it that way?

527
00:18:00,560 --> 00:18:02,160
I think if I want to understand China,

528
00:18:02,400 --> 00:18:03,520
we first of all must understand farmers.

529
00:18:05,600 --> 00:18:06,160
Mr. Shouchang.

530
00:18:07,280 --> 00:18:09,520
I have a question I want to ask you.

531
00:18:09,600 --> 00:18:10,080
Go on.

532
00:18:10,480 --> 00:18:11,440
I've always thought

533
00:18:11,920 --> 00:18:14,080
that the image of industrial workers in our country is particularly high.

534
00:18:14,560 --> 00:18:15,280
But why

535
00:18:15,360 --> 00:18:17,120
are their lives so hard?

536
00:18:18,640 --> 00:18:20,160
This is the difference between China's national conditions

537
00:18:20,560 --> 00:18:22,560
and those of Japan and even Europe.

538
00:18:23,120 --> 00:18:25,200
Although I have never been abroad, I know

539
00:18:25,440 --> 00:18:26,880
that there is no comparison between our country's level of industrialization

540
00:18:27,360 --> 00:18:28,400
and theirs.

541
00:18:29,120 --> 00:18:30,240
In the European revolutions,

542
00:18:30,480 --> 00:18:32,560
the working class is at the center.

543
00:18:32,720 --> 00:18:34,000
For example, the Paris Commune

544
00:18:34,240 --> 00:18:35,360
and the Russian October Revolution

545
00:18:35,600 --> 00:18:37,120
are centered around the working class

546
00:18:37,280 --> 00:18:38,720
in the city centers.

547
00:18:39,040 --> 00:18:40,800
The working class in Europe

548
00:18:40,960 --> 00:18:43,280
is the most conscious, the most disciplined,

549
00:18:43,440 --> 00:18:44,800
and most united class.

550
00:18:45,120 --> 00:18:46,640
I think the workers in our country are not simple either.

551
00:18:47,120 --> 00:18:48,880
Although they are not highly educated,

552
00:18:49,280 --> 00:18:50,400
life is also hard.

553
00:18:50,640 --> 00:18:51,840
But they are still very concerned

554
00:18:51,920 --> 00:18:52,640
about our country.

555
00:18:53,360 --> 00:18:55,200
Some of their words touched me very much today.

556
00:18:57,200 --> 00:18:57,760
It's raining.

